The paper deals with the task of unsupervised learning of 3D representations from natural images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for this task, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of 3D features and transformations, which are relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the disentanglement of 3D pose and identity, which is a problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
